'''1,2-dioleoyl-sn-glycerophosphoethanolamine ''' is a non-bilayer lipid that adopts non-lamellar reverse hexagonal structures.<ref name="MyUser_Sciencedirect.com_September_10_2015c">{{cite journal |url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0005273604001610 |title=Membrane proteins, lipids and detergents: not just a soap opera |date=  |author= |accessdate= September 10, 2015 |doi=10.1016/j.bbamem.2004.04.011 |volume=1666 |journal=Biochimica et Biophysica Acta (BBA) - Biomembranes |pages=105–117|year=2004 |last1=Seddon |first1=Annela M |last2=Curnow |first2=Paul |last3=Booth |first3=Paula J }}</ref>

